# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Updated 2026-04-22 alongside Dockerfile.production CB-3/CB-4 fix:
# the prod modules stage now runs `npm ci && tsc && node postbuild.js` from
# source instead of trusting the in-tree merged data/modules/index.js. So
# we MUST allow package.json, package-lock.json, tsconfig.json and src/
# into the build context, otherwise the COPY in [modules 3/7] fails with
# "/data/modules/package.json: not found" (build #191 hit this).
#
# Items intentionally still excluded:
#   • data/modules/build/        — tsc output regenerated inside the image
#   • data/modules/node_modules/ — installed inside the image
#   • data/modules/*.bak         — local editor backups
#   • data/modules/*.md          — docs not needed at runtime
#   • data/modules_test/         — test fixtures
#   • data/runtime/              — deleted in CB-5; keep ignore in case a
#                                  branch reintroduces it
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
data/modules/build/
# Negation: the dev Dockerfile jsbuilder stage prefers the in-tree
# build/index.js when present so postbuild can run before tsc finishes
# in CI. Prod always re-runs tsc itself, but keeping this negation makes
# the dev / prod paths converge on the same input set.
!data/modules/build/index.js
data/modules/node_modules/
data/modules/*.bak
data/modules/*.md
data/modules/NAKAMA_MODULE_FIX_VERIFICATION.md
data/modules_test/
data/runtime/
